{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Rows with missing required fields are rejected and appear in the dead-letter queue with the original row number.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The failure boundary is between CSV parsing (row index), schema validation, and DLQ writing. A unit test of validator logic alone can miss wiring bugs where row numbers are shifted or DLQ payloads are malformed.","test_description":"Run the ingestion flow on a small CSV fixture with known missing required fields across different line positions. Use real parser + validator + DLQ repository implementation (local test backing store). Assert each invalid row is absent from the normalized output and present in DLQ with exact original CSV row number and raw row payload.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The transformation correctly converts date strings in multiple formats (ISO 8601, US, European) to a single canonical format.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"This is format-conversion logic inside the transformation function. The core failure is parsing/normalization rules, not module wiring or external I/O.","test_description":"Table-driven test for the date normalization function with inputs in ISO 8601, US, and European formats (including edge dates and invalid values). Assert exact canonical output string (or expected parse failure) for each case.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.88,"Integration":0.1,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"A CSV file with 500,000 rows completes processing within the configured timeout without running out of memory.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"The failure boundary is runtime behavior under load: memory growth, GC pressure, and timeout in real process execution. Mocked or narrow tests can hide OOM/throughput failures.","test_description":"Execute the pipeline as a real process against a generated 500k-row CSV and realistic sink configuration, with production-like timeout. Measure wall-clock completion and peak RSS; assert completion before timeout and memory stays below limit without process termination.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.22,"System":0.75,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"When the S3 bucket returns a transient 503 error, the pipeline retries with exponential backoff rather than failing the entire batch.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"This behavior depends on real HTTP error handling and retry timing behavior at the S3 client boundary. Pure mocks can mask transport-layer and retry-policy integration issues.","test_description":"Run the pipeline against an HTTP-backed S3-compatible endpoint/test double that returns 503 for initial requests then succeeds. Verify request attempt count, increasing backoff intervals, and eventual batch success without marking whole batch failed.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.22,"System":0.73,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"Rows successfully written to PostgreSQL are not duplicated if the pipeline is restarted mid-batch.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The failure boundary is idempotency across pipeline state + PostgreSQL writes. Requires real DB semantics and checkpoint/write coordination, but not necessarily OS-level crash orchestration.","test_description":"Use real PostgreSQL in test environment with schema/keys matching production. Process a batch, inject an interruption after part of the batch is committed, then start a fresh pipeline instance with persisted checkpoint state. Assert final row count equals unique source rows and no duplicates exist for business key/primary key.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.12,"Integration":0.58,"System":0.3,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}}]}
